<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138792" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera trigona r. convexiuscula Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona r. convexiuscula Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="trigona" subSpecies="convexiuscula">Ponera trigona Mayr, r. convexiuscula</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="subSpecies">nov. st.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="60">
- [[ worker ]]. - Long. 2,7 a 2,8 mill. - Differe du type americain et specialement de la var. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138876" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opacior">opacior</taxonomicName>
For., a laquelle cette variete ressemble enormement, par les caracteres suivants: La tete n'est pas retrecie derriere (un peu retrecie, et avec les cotes plus convexes chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228145" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Ponera trigona" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigona">trigona</taxonomicName>
). Les scapes n'atteignent pas tout a fait le bord occipital (le depassent plutot un peu chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228145" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Ponera trigona" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigona">trigona</taxonomicName>
). Chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228145" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Ponera trigona" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigona">trigona</taxonomicName>
, le profil de la moitie posterieure du dos du thorax est rectiligne ou un peu convexe; chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:230212" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera trigona r. convexiuscula Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera convexiuscula Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexiuscula">convexiuscula</taxonomicName>
, il est legerement convexe et la face declive du metanotum a des bords moins accentues. La couleur est noire avec les pattes, les antennes et les mandibules rougeatres. La sculpture, surtout sur la tete, est plus forte, meme que chez la variete 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138876" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opacior">opacior</taxonomicName>
. Comme chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228145" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Ponera trigona" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigona">trigona</taxonomicName>
, l' abdomen n'est presque pas retreci apres son premier segment. Les mandibules sont plus larges que chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:228145" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uploaded - Ponera trigona" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trigona">trigona</taxonomicName>
i. sp., mais a peine plus que chez la var. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138876" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" lsidName-HNS="Ponera trigona var. opacior Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opacior">opacior</taxonomicName>
. L'ecaille est bien plus large et la taille plus grande que chez la 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:138789" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ponera confinis Roger" lsidName-HNS="Ponera confinis Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confinis">confinis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="61">L'ensemble de ces differences, dont chacune est bien peu marquee, constitue une race nouvelle de ce groupe presque inextricable. J'en deplore la naissance sans pouvoir l'empecher.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="61">Mackay, Queensland (Turner).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
